    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan before we proceed:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n**5 files to create/modify**, all following the established `next/server` / `userAgent` patterns exactly.\n\n---\n\n### 1. `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` *(new — core impl)*\n- `Geo` interface: `city?`, `country?`, `countryCode?`, `region?`, `latitude?`, `longitude?`, `timezone?`\n- `COUNTRY_NAMES` map for 10 codes (US, GB, DE, FR, JP, CN, IN, BR, AU, CA)\n- `geoFromHeaders(headers)` — reads Vercel headers, falls back to `cf-ipcountry`, derives `country` from map; `null` → `undefined` via `|| undefined`\n- `geo({ headers })` — thin wrapper (mirrors `userAgent` signature)\n- `isInRegion(geo, regions)` — case-insensitive `countryCode` membership check\n- `geoDistance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2)` — Haversine formula, returns km\n\n### 2. `packages/next/geo.js` *(new — CJS entry point)*\nDual-export pattern identical to `server.js`: creates an object, sets `module.exports`, then re-assigns each named `exports.*`.\n\n### 3. `packages/next/geo.d.ts` *(new — TypeScript entry point)*\nRe-exports all 5 symbols from `next/dist/server/web/spec-extension/geo`; `Geo` uses `export type`.\n\n### 4. `packages/next/package.json` *(modified — `files` array only)*\nAdds `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` (alphabetical position: g between f and h).\n\n### 5. `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` *(new — unit tests)*\nUses **Node.js built-in `node:test` + `node:assert/strict`** (no Jest). Covers: full Vercel-header extraction, missing-header → `undefined`, Cloudflare fallback, header precedence, `isInRegion` case-insensitivity, Haversine NY→London ~5570 km ±50, same-point → 0, all 10 country name lookups, unknown code → `country: undefined`.\n\n**Verification:** `pnpm --filter=next types` → `pnpm --filter=next build` → `node --test packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts`",
